The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DAY IV HIGHLIGHTS
                                                DAY IV HIGHLIGHTS
                      
	 Ricky Pontings century stand with Michael Clarke  for the 4th wicket  saw him involve in 64 hundred partnerships, joining Steve Waugh. Only Rahul Dravid (71) and Sachin Tendulkar (66) have more.         
	 This was Pontings 34th Test hundred  his 14th as captain and first as skipper against India. Allan Border and Steve Waugh (15 each) have most hundreds as captain in Tests.         
	 Pontings hundred came after nine Tests and 14 innings. His last hundred also came at the Adelaide Oval (vs England in 2006-07).         
	 Three Australian batsmen scored centuries in the first innings. It was 25th such instance for the home team and the fourth time against India in Tests. The last time they did it so was in then Madras (1986-87) in a tied Test. In other two instances (Adelaide, 1947-48) and Melbourne (1967-68) India suffered innings defeats.         
	 Irfan Pathan after dismissing Brett Lee became the 16th Indian to take 100 or more Test wickets. He also became the seventh Indian allrounder to make 1000 runs and take 100 wickets.           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                    
